GOD BLESS GENTRIFICATION!! It even results in a better Subway restaurant, one where the staff are obviously used to accommodating the reasonable requests of informed consumers who have a choice where to spend their money: unlike the typical fast-food outpost in many an NYC ghetto, we not only don't have bums taking up precious seating with no protest from management, we have workers here who actually try to give you the sandwich fixings you want and are entitled to have by Subway corporate parent policy!! Unfortunately, still not deserving of a perfect five-star rating due to the usual Subway restaurant afflictions -- unnecessarily dirty tables and absolutely no restrooms...looks like the surrounding nabe's gotta gentrify a whole lot more!!
